            <title>[JCR-1599] LuceneQueryBuilder assumes readability of root-Node to be granted in any case.</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/JCR-1599</link>
                <project id="10591" key="JCR">Jackrabbit Content Repository</project>
                        <description>Have a User U. &lt;br/&gt;
Have the User U denied to read &amp;quot;/&amp;quot;.&lt;br/&gt;
Have the User U allowed to read &amp;quot;/home/u&amp;quot;.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
Any query of User U on this workspace fails with an AccessDeniedException.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
The exception is caused by a call insided LuceneQueryBuilder on ln212:&lt;br/&gt;
NodeId id = ((NodeImpl) session.getRootNode()).getNodeId(); &lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
I couldn&amp;#39;t find a specification that imposes the readability of root-node as a precondtion for query.&lt;br/&gt;
Therefore I consider this behavior as a bug.</description>
